\pi \cot \pi \tau = \pi i - 2 \pi i \sum_{m=1}^{\infty} q^m
\tau
q=e^{2 \pi i \tau}
\cot \pi \tau = \frac{\cos \pi \tau}{\sin \pi \tau}
\sin \pi \tau = \frac{e^{\pi \tau i} - e^{-\pi \tau i}}{2i}
\cos \pi \tau = \frac{e^{\pi \tau i} + e^{-\pi \tau i}}{2}
 \pi i - 2 \pi i \sum_{m=1}^{\infty} q^m = \pi i - 2\pi i(\frac{1}{1-q}-1) \\ = \pi i - 2 \pi i (\frac{-q}{1-q}) = \pi i \frac{1+q}{1-q} \\ =  \pi i \frac{1+e^{2\pi i \tau}}{1-e^{2\pi i \tau}} = \pi \cot\pi \tau. 
